# DOE Kit: declared intentional-divergence manifest
# Used by execution/audit_sync.py to separate DELIBERATE local divergence
# from accidental drift. Any kit-managed file you intentionally keep
# different from the kit goes here; everything else that differs is
# reported as DRIFT (sync it back via /sync-doe, or declare it here).
#
# Copy this file to `.doe-overrides` (gitignored) and list the paths your
# project deliberately forks. Each clone has its own manifest -- nothing
# here ships across projects.
#
# Format: one project-relative path per line, as audit_sync reports it
# (e.g. `.claude/hooks/foo.py`, `directives/bar.md`, `commands/baz.md`).
# A trailing slash matches a whole directory prefix. Lines starting with
# `#` are comments; an inline `  # reason` trailer is recommended.
#
# Examples (delete and replace with your actual overrides):
# .claude/hooks/block_dangerous_commands.py  # project adds 2 repo-specific patterns
# directives/security-rules.md               # stricter auth rules for this codebase
# execution/build.py                         # project-specific build, never upstreamed
